title: PML-N Masood Ali Khan wins PB-6 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Masood Ali Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-6, Dukki by securing 10,377 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner up was an Independent candidate Sardar Muhammad Anwar Khan Nasir who bagged 9,804 votes.
Overall voters turn out remained 76.52 percent.
